sources.name: container_terminated
sources.query: ts(kubernetes.pod_container.status, cluster="${cluster_name}" and namespace_name="${namespace}" and pod_name="${a_grouping}*" and status="terminated")

sources.name: A
sources.query: ts(kubernetes*, cluster="${cluster_name}" and namespace_name="${namespace}" and pod_name="${a_grouping}*" and *="Crash*")

sources.name: container_terminated
sources.query: sum(ts(kubernetes.pod_container.status, cluster="${cluster_name}" and namespace_name="${namespace}" and pod_name="${a_grouping}*" and status="waiting"), cluster, pod_name, container_name, namespace_name, reason, status)

sources.name: A
sources.query: ts(kubernetes.pod_container.status, cluster="${cluster_name}" and namespace_name="${namespace}" and pod_name="${a_grouping}*" and reason="Crash*")

charts.name: PODs CPUUsage

sources.name: cpu_used
sources.query: aliasMetric(ts("kubernetes.pod.cpu.usage_rate", cluster="${cluster_name}" and namespace_name="${namespace}" and type="pod"  and pod_name="${a_grouping}*").gt(0), "Used")

sources.name: cpu_request
sources.query: aliasMetric(max(ts("kubernetes.pod.cpu.request", cluster="${cluster_name}" and namespace_name="${namespace}" and type="pod" and pod_name="${a_grouping}*" )), "Request")

sources.name: cpu_limit
sources.query: aliasMetric(max(ts("kubernetes.pod.cpu.limit", cluster="${cluster_name}" and namespace_name="${namespace}" and type="pod"  and pod_name="${a_grouping}*")), "Limit")
